                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d557">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/7128: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-03-01T15:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1926—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 1—6:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>101. My 92, February 26, noon. American consul general, Canton, reports February
                    28, 10 a.m., that presence of destroyer no longer necessary and he has so
                    advised Navy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
